Class AbstractTargetProcessorUpdateIssues

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IProcessorWithTargetName, ITargetProcessorUpdateIssues, ICLIOptionDefinitionProvider, IProcessor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractTargetProcessorUpdateIssuesWithTransitions

    public abstract class AbstractTargetProcessorUpdateIssues
extends AbstractTargetProcessor
implements ITargetProcessorUpdateIssues

    This abstract IProcessor implementation can update issue state for previously submitted issues, based on possibly updated vulnerability data. Based on our superclass AbstractTargetProcessor, we first group all previously submitted vulnerabilities by the corresponding external system issue link, and then update the bug tracker issue based on current vulnerability state.

    Concrete implementations can override the following methods to add support for the corresponding functionality:
    • updateIssueFieldsIfNecessary(Context, TargetIssueLocatorAndFields, LinkedHashMap): Update existing issue fields with updated values
    • openIssueIfClosed(Context, TargetIssueLocatorAndFields): (Re-)open an issue if it is currently closed but corresponding vulnerabilities are still open
    • closeIssueIfOpen(Context, TargetIssueLocatorAndFields): Close an issue if it is currently open but corresponding vulnerabilities have been closed/fixed
    Note that if a bug tracker uses transitioning schemes for managing issue state, it would be better to subclass AbstractTargetProcessorUpdateIssuesWithTransitions instead, as it allows for configurable state transitions to open and close issues.
    Author:
    Ruud Senden
